    "body": "Following up on this though, this presents an annoying issue if you do want to exclude rows based on what the index would look like when run through read_csv (so that the first non-header row is indexed 0).\r\n\r\nWe had a process in which we had to upload a few columns from a CSV to THEN determine which rows from the same CSV we wanted all columns for.\r\n\r\nThe solution we had to use was:\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport pandas as pd\r\n\r\ndf_initial = pd.read_csv('example_csv', delimiter=',', header=0)\r\n\r\n# Code to figure out that the rows we wanted to skip were indexed 0, 3, 5, 7, ...\r\n\r\nrows_to_skip = [0,3,5,7,...]\r\n\r\ndf = pd.read_csv('example_csv', delimiter=',', header=0, skiprows=[x+1 for x in rows_to_skip])\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs there an easier way to do this, or can the skiprows be updated to re-index if header=0 is specified?"
  }
